If you set a space to use the same theme as the site default by using the theme name rather than the 'default' radio button, the global custom CSS is no longer applied.

Steps to reproduce:

# As an administrator, add a custom stylesheet for the whole site.  I would suggest something obvious like the following: {code}p {border: 1px solid #00ff00; }{code}
# Set the site theme to "Clickr"
# Open another space that uses the site default theme and which does not have it's own space stylesheet.  The global css is obviously taking effect.
# Under "Space Admin", set the space theme to "Clickr" rather than default. 

The global style rules immediately stop taking effect.

The reporter (Adaptavist) theorised that this was a result of this code in the DefaultStylesheetManager:

{code}
public String getSpaceStylesheet(String spaceKey, boolean shouldLookGlobal)
    {
        if (!StringUtils.isEmpty(spaceKey) && !StringUtils.isEmpty(themeManager.getSpaceThemeKey(spaceKey)))
        {
            shouldLookGlobal = false;
        }

        // Try to retrieve the stylesheet for a space. If no stylesheet can be founutod, take the global stylesheet
        return (String) bandanaManager.getValue(new ConfluenceBandanaContext(spaceKey), ConfluenceBandanaKeys.CUSTOM_CSS, shouldLookGlobal);
    }
{code}

Their suggestion was that modifying the code as follows would produce the expected results:

{code}
public String getSpaceStylesheet(String spaceKey, boolean shouldLookGlobal)
    {
        if (!StringUtils.isEmpty(spaceKey) && !StringUtils.isEmpty(themeManager.getSpaceThemeKey(spaceKey)) && !themeManager.getSpaceThemeKey(spaceKey).equals(themeManager.getGlobalThemeKey()))
        {
            shouldLookGlobal = false;
        }

        // Try to retrieve the stylesheet for a space. If no stylesheet can be founutod, take the global stylesheet
        return (String) bandanaManager.getValue(new ConfluenceBandanaContext(spaceKey), ConfluenceBandanaKeys.CUSTOM_CSS, shouldLookGlobal);
    }
{code}

