We have a ton of spaces and are working to make navigation easier.  I have defined team labels for the spaces.  In addition, I am creating customized navigational pages (essentially sub-dashboards) for each of these teams and I wanted to duplicate the functionality on the main dashboard to include a space list and recently updated content relevant to each team page.  

I did figure out a way to display recently updated content relevant to the team.  Unfortunately, there was no way to define a team view for the "spaces" macro so that it would not retain the last chosen team value from somewhere else on the site, such as the main dashboard.  Therefore, I altered the code in SpacesListMacro.java to provide the functionality I needed.

I attached the altered file to this JIRA.  The code section containing modifications is indicated with "BEGIN" and "END" comments.  I would like to see this change incorporated into supported releases of the Dashboard Macros Plugin.  I did not have enough time to figure out the dynamic relationship between the "spaces" macro and the "recently-updated" macro, but I would like the "recently updated - team spaces" view on each sub-page to dynamically change based on the default team chosen.  I am able to work around that restriction by defining the individual space keys for each team, but this will prove to be a maintenance nuisance.

* *Original Source File:*  http://svn.atlassian.com/svn/public/contrib/confluence/confluence-dashboard-macros/tags/confluence-dashboard-macros-1.6/src/main/java/com/atlassian/confluence/plugins/macros/dashboard/SpacesListMacro.java

* *Updated Source File:*  _attached to this JIRA_

* *Invoke Macro to display a particular team:*
 {code}{spaces:team=corporate|width=100%}{code}

